    <div class="bit-60"> 
     <h2 class="transfer-2">Next Steps for Admitted Students</h2> 
     <h5>Celebrate</h5> 
     <p>All your hard work has paid off! Enjoy the moment and take time to pray about your decision.</p> 
     <a id="visit"></a>
     <h5>Visit Westmont</h5> 
     <p>If you can’t attend Admitted Student Days and haven’t visited our campus, you need to see it for yourself. For more information and to schedule a visit, go to the <a href="https://secure.westmont.edu/forms/admissions/admitted_students/index_new.php?type=asd" target="_blank" class="maroon">visit page</a>.</p> 
     <a id="asd"></a>
     <h5>Attend Admitted Student Days March 6-7 or April 10-11</h5> 
     <p>Learn more about Westmont and meet our faculty and students at Admitted Student Days. Participate in class, worship in chapel, stay overnight in the residence halls, and more. Ever if you've visited before, this event will provide a deeper experience of life at Westmont. Bring the whole family! </p> 
     <div class="btn">
      <a href="/admissions/visit.html" target="_blank"><img src="images/btn-register.png" alt="register button" width="50%"></a>
     </div> 
     <h5>File Financial Aid Forms</h5> 
     <p> Make certain all financial aid forms have been filed. The FAFSA should be submitted between January 1 and March 2. If you are a California resident, remember your GPA Verification form. In March, all admitted students who have submitted their FAFSA <a href="https://fafsa.ed.gov/" target="_blank" class="maroon">(fafsa.ed.gov)</a> information to Westmont will receive an email with instructions on how to view their financial aid package. This email will be directed to whichever email address the student listed on the application. If you have any questions, please feel free to contact the Financial Aid Office at 805-565-6063 or <a href="mailto:finaid@westmont.edu" class="maroon">finaid@westmont.edu</a>.</p> 
